<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<title>MKTG 4333 · Chapter 1 · AI Foundations deck</title>
<style>
  :root{
    --bg:#f5f2ec; --ink:#1a1a1a; --ink-soft:#4A4A4A; --ink-mute:#7A7A7A;
    --rule:#E8E6E1; --accent:#DA7756; --accent-tint:#FDF6F3;
    --font:'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
  }
  *{ margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
  html,body{ background:var(--bg); font-family:var(--font); color:var(--ink); }
  body{ padding:64px 72px 96px; }
  header{
    display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:flex-end;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); padding-bottom:20px; margin-bottom:36px;
  }
  header .dot{ display:inline-block; width:10px; height:10px; background:var(--accent); border-radius:50%; margin-right:10px; vertical-align:middle; }
  header h1{ font-size:32px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:-0.01em; }
  header h1 em{ font-style:italic; color:var(--accent); font-weight:500; }
  header .meta{
    font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.12em; text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--ink-mute); font-weight:600;
  }
  .intro{
    max-width:70ch; font-size:18px; line-height:1.55; color:var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom:44px;
  }
  .intro a{ color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; border-bottom:1px solid var(--accent); }
  .grid{
    display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(420px, 1fr));
    gap:28px;
  }
  .card{
    background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rule);
    display:flex; flex-direction:column; overflow:hidden;
    transition: transform .2s, box-shadow .2s;
  }
  .card:hover{ transform:translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 8px 24px -10px rgba(0,0,0,.15); }
  .card .frame{
    position:relative; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; overflow:hidden; background:#ffffff;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .card .frame .scaler{
    position:absolute; top:0; left:0;
    width:960px; height:540px;
    transform-origin: top left;
  }
  .card .frame iframe{
    width:960px; height:540px; border:0; display:block; pointer-events:none;
    background:#ffffff;
  }
  .card .info{ padding:16px 22px; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:baseline; gap:12px; }
  .card .info h3{ font-size:16px; font-weight:600; line-height:1.3; }
  .card .info .n{
    font-size:11px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:0.14em; color:var(--ink-mute);
    text-transform:uppercase; white-space:nowrap;
  }
  .card .info .tmpl{ display:block; font-size:12px; color:var(--ink-soft); margin-top:3px; font-style:italic; }
  .card a.open{
    display:block; text-align:right; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.12em;
    text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600;
    padding:0 22px 16px; text-decoration:none;
  }
  footer{
    margin-top:64px; padding-top:20px; border-top:1px solid var(--rule);
    font-size:13px; color:var(--ink-mute); display:flex; justify-content:space-between;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1><span class="dot"></span>Chapter 1 · <em>AI Foundations</em>.</h1>
    <span class="meta">MKTG 4333 · 20 slides · 960 × 540</span>
  </header>

  <p class="intro">
    A teaching deck on the prerequisite AI primer, built on the coral design system. One claim per slide, white
    backgrounds, one coral element per slide, Segoe UI throughout. It pairs with the Chapter 1 chapter and runs the
    same arc: the opening 67-percent failure, the context window and silent truncation, RAG, the model as a
    well-read autocomplete, hallucination, the five prompt moves, the knowledge cutoff versus live search, the
    agent loop, the no-code specialist and the Skill, the MCP plug, the four-rung ladder (ask, save, connect,
    schedule), what the top rung costs, four real brands on the ladder, the four failure modes with AI overreliance
    underneath, and the diagnostic students carry into the client project. Read the system rules in
    <a href="../DESIGN-SYSTEM.md">DESIGN-SYSTEM.md</a> and
    <a href="../CHART-PRINCIPLES.md">CHART-PRINCIPLES.md</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="grid" id="grid"></div>

<script>
(() => {
  const slides = [
    ["01-title.html",            "01", "AI is the file, the wire, the model, the agent, and the stack", "Title / cover"],
    ["02-divider-opening.html",  "02", "A confident summary covered only the slice that fit", "Section divider"],
    ["03-opening-failure.html",  "03", "Eight thousand rows in, the model read to row 3,800 and reported 67% on a guess", "Content · running example"],
    ["04-context-window.html",   "04", "A file is read in chunks, and a chunk past the context-window ceiling never arrives", "Exhibit · chapter file-vs-window"],
    ["05-rag.html",              "05", "Point the model at your own trusted documents first, and grounding cuts the wrong answer", "Exhibit · RAG"],
    ["06-divider-model.html",    "06", "The model is a well-read autocomplete", "Section divider"],
    ["07-hallucination.html",    "07", "The model reaches for the most natural-sounding next word, not the most truthful one", "Content"],
    ["08-prompt-moves.html",     "08", "Each move climbs the answer-quality bar; the win is the context you hand over", "Exhibit · chapter prompt moves"],
    ["09-cutoff-vs-search.html", "09", "A frozen memory answers from training; a live web search answers from today", "Two-column"],
    ["10-divider-agent.html",    "10", "An agent is the model put in a loop with tools", "Section divider"],
    ["11-agent-loop.html",       "11", "The agent runs one loop: think, use a tool, read, decide, until the job is done", "Exhibit · chapter agent loop"],
    ["12-nocode-vs-skill.html",  "12", "A no-code specialist takes ten minutes; a Skill is the more powerful next step", "Two-column"],
    ["13-mcp.html",              "13", "One shared plug lets any assistant reach every connected app", "Exhibit · MCP port"],
    ["14-divider-stack.html",    "14", "The stack is a four-rung climb", "Section divider"],
    ["15-the-ladder.html",       "15", "Climb the ladder and the same model does more while you do less", "Exhibit · chapter four-rung ladder"],
    ["16-cost.html",             "16", "A weekly agent reads three pages and posts a brief for about $16 a year", "KPI row"],
    ["17-four-brands.html",      "17", "Four brands, four stopping points; the rung tells you what each trusts a machine to do", "KPI row"],
    ["18-failure-modes.html",    "18", "Four parts, four quiet breaks; AI overreliance sits under all of them", "Content · failure modes"],
    ["19-apply-diagnostic.html", "19", "Run the four parts on one real file you actually have", "Content · diagnostic"],
    ["20-closing.html",          "20", "Hold the five parts and the rest of the book has its floor", "Closing / takeaways"]
  ];
  const grid = document.getElementById('grid');
  slides.forEach(([href, n, claim, tmpl]) => {
    const card = document.createElement('article');
    card.className = 'card';
    card.innerHTML =
      '<div class="frame"><div class="scaler"><iframe src="' + href + '?thumb=1" title="' + claim + '"></iframe></div></div>' +
      '<div class="info"><div><h3>' + claim + '</h3><span class="tmpl">' + tmpl + '</span></div><span class="n">' + n + '</span></div>' +
      '<a class="open" href="' + href + '" target="_blank">Open &rarr;</a>';
    grid.appendChild(card);
  });

  function fitCards(){
    document.querySelectorAll('.card .frame').forEach(frame => {
      const scaler = frame.querySelector('.scaler');
      if (!scaler) return;
      const w = frame.clientWidth;
      const s = w / 960;
      scaler.style.transform = 'scale(' + s + ')';
      scaler.style.width  = '960px';
      scaler.style.height = '540px';
      frame.style.height = (540 * s) + 'px';
    });
  }
  document.querySelectorAll('iframe').forEach(f => {
    f.addEventListener('load', () => {
      try { f.contentDocument.documentElement.classList.add('is-thumb'); } catch(_){}
    });
  });
  window.addEventListener('resize', fitCards);
  window.addEventListener('load', fitCards);
  fitCards();
})();
</script>

  <footer>
    <span>MKTG 4333 · Prof. Felipe M. Affonso · Spears School of Business</span>
    <span>White bg · Segoe UI · one coral accent · pairs with the Ch 1 chapter</span>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
